Not impressed. For a location so central, so close to downtown and the subway, they should get all the basics right.  First and most importantly, it's way too cold. They crank up the A/C to insane levels.. I would guess 67 degrees or lower, which is not a comfortable indoor temperature (70 would be better). When I asked the staff member about it she said she was "not the right person to ask about it" because she didn't feel cold. What am I supposed to do with that? Conduct a random sample of the other employees and petition for a redress of grievances? Responses including "I'm not allowed adjust the thermostat," "I'll let you speak with a manager," and "I recommend trying a different location" would have helped solve my problem.  Not a helpful response. The employee deflected my question rather than taking responsibility.  I left because my hands were literally numbing up.  There seem to be quite a few incidents where customers quarrel with staff.. and the staff didn't seem to handle it particularly well.. usually Starbucks will fix up your drink, no questions asked, but the staff seemed a little sassy.  There are a few tables, and a bar by the window, but not enough for a busy downtown location.
